Yet, for many, the stigma of mental illness remains, and those in the church with diagnoses often suffer in silence.
Her story is told in Kate Fagan’s excellent new book, What Made Maddy Run: The Secret Struggles and Tragic Death of an All-American Teen.
Naming the despair that can accompany mental illness can be difficult work, as can walking alongside those facing the challenges of parenting a teen with a mental illness.
And churches need to stay connected to the young adults in their congregations once they graduate high school and move on.
Fagan’s What Made Maddy Run makes this point clear.